data.description: Here is your chance to own a piece of Canton history! This home will wow you with the charm and unique features it offers. This home was custom built by a former Champion Paper Mill management employee. Home was had some remodeling done since, but many of the original features were preserved. Entering the home, you'll find a large living room which opens to the dining room. Note the tall ceilings and spacious feeling. Larger kitchen for the time period in which the home was built. Primary bedroom on main with huge bathroom. Another full bathroom on the main as well. Two staircases to go upstairs. 3 spacious bedrooms and a full bathroom await upstairs. Notice the private stairway and sink in a bedroom? Former nanny quarters, super cool! Home also sits on one of the largest lots in the neighborhood. Lots of outdoor space from the balcony, deck, front porch. Come see this one today!
